@r I would say it is intuitive in the same sense as left click is to open a notification. There is precedence for this behaviour (many games, browser extensions, etc.), albeit not in gnome.

@exalm I wasn't aware this was a touch only issue. Should I create a new ticket to discuss this?

Do you mean the `filename` in 

    xmlReadFile(filename, NULL, 0);

should be percent encoded? It doesn't seem to work with percent encoded filenames. Also, it returns `1%3Ab.xml` for both the files `1:b.xml` and `1%3Ab.xml`, so I'm not sure *when* to percent decode the URL.
